value.value: 原腸形成異常
any anomaly in the development and invagination of the embryonic germ layers

definition.value: in the mouse, gastrulation initiates at E6.5, as cells of the primitive ectoderm (epiblast) delaminate at the posterior side of the embryo and ingress through the primitive streak in an epithelial-to-mesenchymal transition

value.value: 原腸形成不全
inability to differentiate and invaginate the primary germ layers
胚サイズの異常
any anomaly in the proportions of embryo compared to littermates (sensu Mus: up to E14, or the completion of organogenesis)
胚サイズの減少
smaller proportions of an embryo compared to littermates or other controls (sensu Mus: up to E14, or the completion of organogenesis)
胚サイズの増大
larger proportions of embryo compared to littermates or other controls (sensu Mus: up to E14, or the completion of organogenesis)
胚葉回転の異常

atypical axial rotation of the germ layers of the embryo during the primitive streak/early somite stage during which the curvature of the entire trunk region is normally reversed and the neural ectoderm moves to the convex region and the midgut region becomes located in the concave region

definition.value: In mouse, this event occurs at E8.5-E9.5.

value.value: 胚葉回転の不全
arrest of the axial rotation of the germ layers of the embryo during the primitive streak/early somite stage

definition.value: In mouse, this event occurs at E8.5-E9.5.

value.value: 背腹軸形成異常
anomaly in the development or formation of the axis that runs from the front to the back surface of the body
先端基部軸形成異常
anomaly in the formation or development of a body structure, often a limb, in relation to the structure's proximity to the trunk or point of origin
左右軸形成異常
anomaly in the formation or development of the body or a specific organ of the body in relation to the left and right sides of the body or organ
羊膜褶欠如
failure of the amnion to form involutions
胎盤形態異常
any structural anomaly of the organ of metabolic interchange between fetus and mother, which is partly of embryonic origin and partly of maternal origin
胎盤発達異常
malformed or incomplete differentiation of the organ of metabolic exchange between the fetus and mother
栄養膜巨細胞数減少
fewer than normal number of cells of the extraembryonic cell layer that contributes to the placenta
栄養膜巨細胞欠如
missing cells of the extraembryonic cell layer that contribute to the placenta
胎盤迷路部形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the placental labyrinth, typically resulting in decreased size
胎盤迷路部形態不全

any structural anomaly of the placental layers where embryonic blood vessels are surrounded by trophoblast cells and maternal blood, and is the site where the exchange of nutrients and waste products occurs between the maternal and fetal circulation
胎盤外円錐欠如
missing the thickened trophoblast of the blastocyst in rodents that becomes the fetal portion of the placenta
臓側卵黄嚢形態異常

any structural anomaly of the extraembryonic tissue membrane, formed from the visceral endoderm and the extraembryonic mesoderm, which is located ventral to the embryonic disc and is connected to the presumptive midgut of the embryo; the yolk that it contains is the site of embryonic hematopoiesis and vitelline circulation is involved in early embryonic circulation; it is the origin of the primordial germ cells
卵黄嚢脈管構造欠如
absence of the vascular network that supplies the yolk sac

label.value: absent visceral yolk sac blood islands

value.value: 臓側卵黄嚢の血島の欠如

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: absent visceral yolk sac blood islands

value.value: absence of the masses of developing blood cells attached to endothelium in the yolk sac
淡色卵黄嚢(血行不良)
bloodless yolk sac
卵黄嚢脈管組織異常
derangement in the pattern of the primary (honeycomb-like) vasculature of the yolk sac prior to remodeling into a mature vascular network
内胚葉由来胚外組織形成異常

malformation of the derivative of the hypoblast cells that migrate into the blastocyst cavity, and line the cavity, giving rise to the primary and definitive yolk sacs; the extraembryonic endoderm fills the remaining cavity of the blastocyst
臍帯形態異常
any structural anomaly of the connective stalk between the fetus and the placenta
尿膜形態異常
any structural anomaly fetal membrane which contributes to the formation of the umbilical cord and placental blood vessels
胚着床異常

anomaly in the process in which the blastocyst and/or the uterine environment to successfully synchronize allowing attachment of the blastocyst to the epithelial lining of the uterus, its penetration through the epithelium and any subsequent physiological interactions necessary to sustain embryonic development
着床不全

inability of the blastocyst and/or the uterine environment to successfully synchronize allowing attachment of the blastocyst to the epithelial lining of the uterus, its penetration through the epithelium and any subsequent physiological interactions necessary to sustain embryonic development
着床障害

impaired ability of the blastocyst and/or the uterine environment to successfully synchronize allowing attachment of the blastocyst to the epithelial lining of the uterus, its penetration through the epithelium and any subsequent physiological interactions necessary to sustain embryonic development
胚発達停止
the cessation of development beyond a particular stage
出生後成長異常
anomaly in reaching a developmental stage or stages after birth
出生後成長遅延
slow or limited development after birth
副腎分泌異常
altered ability of the surparenal gland to produce or secrete hormones
副腎エピネフリン分泌不全
inability of adrenal gland to deliver epinephrine into the blood stream
血中アドレナリン欠如

absence in the circulation of a catecholamine hormone that stimulates the adrenergic receptors and causes systemic vasoconstriction and gastrointestinal relaxation, stimulates the heart, and dilates bronchi and cerebral vessels
血中ノルアドレナリン欠如

absence of the hormone secreted by the adrenal medulla and acts as a neurotransmitter in the sympathetic peripheral nervous system and in some tracts of the CNS; noradrenaline is the demethylated biosynthetic precursor of epinephrine
コルチコステロン分泌過多
increased release of this adrenocortical steroid that induces glycogen deposition and regulates sodium conservation and potassium secretion
コルチコステロン血中濃度上昇
greater than the normal blood amount of an adrenocortical steroid that induces glycogen deposition and regulates sodium conservation and potassium secretion
下垂体分泌異常
anomaly in the production and/or release of biologically active substances from pituitary tissue
副腎皮質刺激ホルモン分泌過多
increased release of this pituitary hormone from the pituitary gland that stimulates the secretion of adrenal cortical steroids and induces growth of the adrenal cortex
副腎皮質刺激ホルモン血中濃度上昇
elevated concentration in the blood of the pituitary hormone that stimulates the secretion of adrenal cortical steroids and induces growth of the adrenal cortex

label.value: suppressed circulating follicle stimulating hormone level

value.value: 血中卵胞刺激ホルモン値抑制

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: suppressed circulating follicle stimulating hormone level

value.value: repression of secretion into the blood of FSH, the hormone that, in females, stimulates the graafian follicles of the ovary and assists in follicular maturation and the secretion of estradiol; in the male it stimulates the epithelium of the seminiferous tubules and is partly responsible for spermatogenesis

label.value: increased circulating follicle stimulating hormone level

value.value: 卵胞刺激ホルモン血中濃度上昇

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: increased circulating follicle stimulating hormone level

value.value: higher than normal levels in the blood stream of FSH, the hormone that, in females, stimulates the graafian follicles of the ovary and assists in follicular maturation and the secretion of estradiol; in the male it stimulates the epithelium of the seminiferous tubules and is partly responsible for spermatogenesis
黄体形成ホルモン血中濃度上昇
higher than the normal levels in the bloodstream of LH, the hormone that regulates steroid production by the interstitial cells of the testis and the ovary
視床下部分泌異常
altered ability of the hypothalamus to produce or release biologically active substances
副腎皮質刺激ホルモン放出ホルモン分泌過多
excessive release of this factor, which normally stimulates the pituitary to release adrenocorticotropic hormone, from the hypothalamus
副腎皮質刺激ホルモン放出ホルモン血中濃度上昇
higher than average amount of CRH in blood; CRH is normally released by the hypothalamus and stimulates the release of corticotropin by the anterior pituitary gland
排尿異常
anomaly in the process in which parasympathetic nerves stimulate the bladder wall muscle to contract resulting in the expulsion of urine from the body
尿中グルコース濃度異常
any change in the amount of glucose in the urine
尿中グルコース濃度上昇
a greater amount of glucose in the urine compared to the normal state
